					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7645481#post-4300131</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7645481/scp-1831#post-4300131</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 07 Jul 2019 05:25:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Spinachguy</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2084624</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I like exploration SCPs, and this one comes at it from a unique angle even though it doesn't actually &quot;explore&quot; anything.</p> <p>Its possible it may not even be a physical location, though, and that would kind of disappoint me.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;My&nbsp;two-cent&nbsp;analysis:</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;My&nbsp;two-cent&nbsp;analysis:</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>His mom was what was protecting him from his father. Whenever the sociopath in him came out, it hurt his mother in some way and his sociopathic side resented Mom. When his mom died, nothing was keeping him from drinking the alcohol and he became more sociopathic/psychotic.</p> <p>The narrator represents ethics and emotion. As is stereotypical of this, he doesn't have a great rote memory, thus the memory gap of [owning one dog] or of [how to fire a BB gun]. He could tell you it took two minutes to count the raindrops, but not how many raindrops there were. Narrator would remember the snack, the brother would know how to prepare the snack. Maybe he only thinks that the sky is white because the picture is all he has as a reference of how things were in reality.</p> <p>That his father forgot to put the lock up for weeks in a row implies to me he died of alcohol poisoning or something similar and the house was too mired in alcohol bottles for him to tell for certain if he was still alive probably. Not without potentially attracting his attention, anyway. Cue lonely downward spiral.</p> <p>The jury is out on if the dad was abusive, or if the mom was a victim of the brother. Dad didn't help, though, with locking up Narrator in the washroom emotionally.</p> <p>The picture is a prison containing the narrator, somehow. Its probably a metaphor for innocence lost in a bad upbringing, in a literary sense. Somewhere, there is a potentially violent sociopath wandering around.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
